        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 4 at 7:16PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 716 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Evergreen, or 13 miles west of Whiteville, moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lumberton, Chadbourn, Bladenboro, Boardman, Smiths, Howellsville,
Bladen Community College, Butters, Hestertown, Barker Ten Mile,
Evergreen, Dublin, Cerro Gordo, and Orrum.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
